messages.content: 911, what's your emergency?
Hi, I'm reporting an airplane crash at SFO.
An airplane crash at SFO?
Yeah, we were hiking on a trail outside of Pacifica, and we just heard a giant explosion. We're with a couple other hikers, and they saw that an airplane had crashed right there at SFO.
Actually, at the airport?
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
What's your name?
My name is Jared Foster.
All right, Jared, hang on the line. I'll transfer you over to the police department at SFO, okay?
Okay, thank you.
911 emergency, what are you reporting?
Hi, there was an airplane crash at SFO.
Okay, we did get the call.
You did?
Yes, we did. We are responding. Trust me.
Okay, thank you. Bye.
911, what's your emergency?
Hi, we're at the San Francisco Airport, and our airplane just crashed upon landing. We need help here as soon as possible.
Okay, what runway are you on?
I don't know the runway. We just ran out of the airplane.
What kind of airplane were you in?
Asiana Airlines.
There's a bunch of fire trucks and a couple of ambulances. There are a lot of people injured, and we need more help.
My name is Sang Duong.
Do you know where on the runway you are?
I see FFP, but I'm looking around trying to see something, but I don't really see much else.
You're in a field?
Yeah, we're in the middle of the runway. I can see the main terminal, but I don't know much more. Sorry, I'm not familiar with this airport.
Okay, hang on the line. Let me get you over there. Don't disconnect.
Okay, I see tons of cops and ambulances coming now, but not too many ambulances.
Okay, we do have ambulances and the fire department on the way. Can you tell me if there are people trapped on the plane?
Most people got off. I think there are at least a handful of people behind me.
Are you guys actually trapped, or are people just slowly getting off?
Most people are off. Some emergency crews are going into the plane now.
Okay, sorry for the misunderstanding. Are the passengers all safely getting off the slide?
Yes, almost everyone is out. The majority of people are out of the airplane.
I don't know the specific runway, but we are next to some wreckage. I see signs that say 'Monitor 120.5.'
That's okay. What kind of aircraft is it?
It's an Asiana plane. Sorry, I'm really not sure.
Got it. Are you safe where you are?
Yes, we're way past the field, at least 100 yards out.
California Highway Patrol, what's your emergency?
Hi, we are at the San Francisco International Airport, and we just got in a plane crash. There are a lot of people that need help.
Are you with any of the ambulances that are there?
No, they haven't found us yet, and there are people here who are burned really badly.
Where are you?
We're out on the outskirts, not towards the airport itself, more in the field where planes land.
Stay on the line. Let me get you over to medical.
Okay.
Ambulance emergency, what's the location of your emergency?
We're at the San Francisco International Airport.
Do you need help?
Yes, we just got in a plane crash, and there are people who still need help. There's not enough medics out here.
We have help on the way. You said there's a woman very severely burned?
Yes, she needs help immediately. She will probably die soon if we don't get help.
Can you confirm your phone number, please?
Where on the runway are you?
We're next to a United airplane near the beginning of the runway where the plane debris is.
How old is she?
About 25 or 24. She's severely burned.
I'll ask you some questions and see if I can provide instructions.
911, what's your emergency?
I'm seeing a fire from the side of the road in Burlingame.
What road are you on?
I'm on 101 North.
Near what exit?
Near Broadway.
Do you see it to the right or left of the freeway?
To the right.
Let me get fire department on the line with us.
Ambulance emergency, what's the location?
We're at the San Francisco International Airport.
Do you need help?
Yes, we just had a plane crash. There are people seriously injured on the tarmac, and we need ambulances here.
We're aware of the situation and have units responding.
There are people laying on the tarmac with critical injuries, and we're trying to help them.
What's your name?
Cindy Stone.
What's the phone number you're calling from, Cindy?
Let me transfer you to San Francisco Medical.
Ambulance emergency, what are you reporting?
Hi, this is CHP with a transfer. She's part of the crash at San Francisco Airport. Go ahead.
Hello? Hello.
